## Memory

All persistent memory lives in `./memory/` inside this repo — **not** in `~/.claude/`. Always read from and write to `./memory/` for this project. The `memory/MEMORY.md` file is the index; individual memory files live alongside it.

Memory format: frontmatter with `name`, `description`, `type` (user/feedback/project/reference), then content body.

## Collaboration Rules

1. **Before starting any task** — if confidence is >=95%, ask one confirming question before implementing. No silent assumptions.
2. **Commit messages** — conventional format: `type: description {{TASK_ID_FORMAT}}`. Types: `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`, `chore:`, `test:`
{{#HAS_REVIEW_GATE}}
3. **After completing a task** — set status to **In Review** (not Completed). {{USER_NAME}} reviews before closing.
{{/HAS_REVIEW_GATE}}
4. **Estimates** — use AI-assisted t-shirt sizes: XS=<15min, S=15-45min, M=45min-2h, L=2-4h. Reference comparable completed tasks.
5. **Retro** — every {{RETRO_CADENCE}}. Write entry to `RETRO.md`, update `memory/retro.md` task count.

## Code Rules

1. Read the depth file ({{DEPTH_FILE}}) before making changes
{{#HAS_SCRIPTS}}
2. `--dry-run` first when testing scripts
